2529 ParmVarDecl *TemplateInstantiator::TransformFunctionTypeParam(
2530  ParmVarDecl *OldParm, int indexAdjustment,
2531  std::optional<unsigned> NumExpansions, bool ExpectParameterPack) {
2532  auto NewParm = SemaRef.SubstParmVarDecl(
2533  OldParm, TemplateArgs, indexAdjustment, NumExpansions,
2534  ExpectParameterPack, EvaluateConstraints);
2535  if (NewParm && SemaRef.getLangOpts().OpenCL)
2536  SemaRef.deduceOpenCLAddressSpace(NewParm);
2537  return NewParm;

2539 
2540 QualType TemplateInstantiator::BuildSubstTemplateTypeParmType(
2541  TypeLocBuilder &TLB, bool SuppressObjCLifetime, bool Final,
2542  Decl *AssociatedDecl, unsigned Index, std::optional<unsigned> PackIndex,
2543  TemplateArgument Arg, SourceLocation NameLoc) {
2544  QualType Replacement = Arg.getAsType();
2545 
2546  // If the template parameter had ObjC lifetime qualifiers,
2547  // then any such qualifiers on the replacement type are ignored.
2548  if (SuppressObjCLifetime) {
2549  Qualifiers RQs;
2550  RQs = Replacement.getQualifiers();
2551  RQs.removeObjCLifetime();
2552  Replacement =
2553  SemaRef.Context.getQualifiedType(Replacement.getUnqualifiedType(), RQs);
2554  }
2555 
2556  if (Final) {
2557  TLB.pushTrivial(SemaRef.Context, Replacement, NameLoc);
2558  return Replacement;
2559  }
2560  // TODO: only do this uniquing once, at the start of instantiation.
2561  QualType Result = getSema().Context.getSubstTemplateTypeParmType(
2562  Replacement, AssociatedDecl, Index, PackIndex);
2563  SubstTemplateTypeParmTypeLoc NewTL =
2564  TLB.push<SubstTemplateTypeParmTypeLoc>(Result);
2565  NewTL.setNameLoc(NameLoc);
2566  return Result;
2567 }
2568 
2569 QualType
2570 TemplateInstantiator::TransformTemplateTypeParmType(TypeLocBuilder &TLB,
2571  TemplateTypeParmTypeLoc TL,
2572  bool SuppressObjCLifetime) {
2573  const TemplateTypeParmType *T = TL.getTypePtr();
2574  if (T->getDepth() < TemplateArgs.getNumLevels()) {
2575  // Replace the template type parameter with its corresponding
2576  // template argument.
2577 
2578  // If the corresponding template argument is NULL or doesn't exist, it's
2579  // because we are performing instantiation from explicitly-specified
2580  // template arguments in a function template class, but there were some
2581  // arguments left unspecified.
2582  if (!TemplateArgs.hasTemplateArgument(T->getDepth(), T->getIndex())) {
2583  TemplateTypeParmTypeLoc NewTL
2584  = TLB.push<TemplateTypeParmTypeLoc>(TL.getType());
2585  NewTL.setNameLoc(TL.getNameLoc());
2586  return TL.getType();
2587  }
2588 
2589  TemplateArgument Arg = TemplateArgs(T->getDepth(), T->getIndex());
2590 
2591  if (TemplateArgs.isRewrite()) {
2592  // We're rewriting the template parameter as a reference to another
2593  // template parameter.
2594  if (Arg.getKind() == TemplateArgument::Pack) {
2595  assert(Arg.pack_size() == 1 && Arg.pack_begin()->isPackExpansion() &&
2596  "unexpected pack arguments in template rewrite");
2597  Arg = Arg.pack_begin()->getPackExpansionPattern();
2598  }
2599  assert(Arg.getKind() == TemplateArgument::Type &&
2600  "unexpected nontype template argument kind in template rewrite");
2601  QualType NewT = Arg.getAsType();
2602  TLB.pushTrivial(SemaRef.Context, NewT, TL.getNameLoc());
2603  return NewT;
2604  }
2605 
2606  auto [AssociatedDecl, Final] =
2607  TemplateArgs.getAssociatedDecl(T->getDepth());
2608  std::optional<unsigned> PackIndex;
2609  if (T->isParameterPack()) {
2610  assert(Arg.getKind() == TemplateArgument::Pack &&
2611  "Missing argument pack");
2612 
2613  if (getSema().ArgumentPackSubstitutionIndex == -1) {
2614  // We have the template argument pack, but we're not expanding the
2615  // enclosing pack expansion yet. Just save the template argument
2616  // pack for later substitution.
2617  QualType Result = getSema().Context.getSubstTemplateTypeParmPackType(
2618  AssociatedDecl, T->getIndex(), Final, Arg);
2619  SubstTemplateTypeParmPackTypeLoc NewTL
2620  = TLB.push<SubstTemplateTypeParmPackTypeLoc>(Result);
2621  NewTL.setNameLoc(TL.getNameLoc());
2622  return Result;
2623  }
2624 
2625  // PackIndex starts from last element.
2626  PackIndex = getPackIndex(Arg);
2627  Arg = getPackSubstitutedTemplateArgument(getSema(), Arg);
2628  }
2629 
2630  assert(Arg.getKind() == TemplateArgument::Type &&
2631  "Template argument kind mismatch");
2632 
2633  return BuildSubstTemplateTypeParmType(TLB, SuppressObjCLifetime, Final,
2634  AssociatedDecl, T->getIndex(),
2635  PackIndex, Arg, TL.getNameLoc());
2636  }
2637 
2638  // The template type parameter comes from an inner template (e.g.,
2639  // the template parameter list of a member template inside the
2640  // template we are instantiating). Create a new template type
2641  // parameter with the template "level" reduced by one.
2642  TemplateTypeParmDecl *NewTTPDecl = nullptr;
2643  if (TemplateTypeParmDecl *OldTTPDecl = T->getDecl())
2644  NewTTPDecl = cast_or_null<TemplateTypeParmDecl>(
2645  TransformDecl(TL.getNameLoc(), OldTTPDecl));
2646  QualType Result = getSema().Context.getTemplateTypeParmType(
2647  T->getDepth() - TemplateArgs.getNumSubstitutedLevels(), T->getIndex(),
2648  T->isParameterPack(), NewTTPDecl);
2649  TemplateTypeParmTypeLoc NewTL = TLB.push<TemplateTypeParmTypeLoc>(Result);
2650  NewTL.setNameLoc(TL.getNameLoc());
2651  return Result;
2652 }
2653 
2654 QualType TemplateInstantiator::TransformSubstTemplateTypeParmPackType(
2655  TypeLocBuilder &TLB, SubstTemplateTypeParmPackTypeLoc TL,
2656  bool SuppressObjCLifetime) {
2657  const SubstTemplateTypeParmPackType *T = TL.getTypePtr();
2658 
2659  Decl *NewReplaced = TransformDecl(TL.getNameLoc(), T->getAssociatedDecl());
2660 
2661  if (getSema().ArgumentPackSubstitutionIndex == -1) {
2662  // We aren't expanding the parameter pack, so just return ourselves.
2663  QualType Result = TL.getType();
2664  if (NewReplaced != T->getAssociatedDecl())
2665  Result = getSema().Context.getSubstTemplateTypeParmPackType(
2666  NewReplaced, T->getIndex(), T->getFinal(), T->getArgumentPack());
2667  SubstTemplateTypeParmPackTypeLoc NewTL =
2668  TLB.push<SubstTemplateTypeParmPackTypeLoc>(Result);
2669  NewTL.setNameLoc(TL.getNameLoc());
2670  return Result;
2671  }
2672 
2673  TemplateArgument Pack = T->getArgumentPack();
2674  TemplateArgument Arg = getPackSubstitutedTemplateArgument(getSema(), Pack);
2675  return BuildSubstTemplateTypeParmType(
2676  TLB, SuppressObjCLifetime, T->getFinal(), NewReplaced, T->getIndex(),
2677  getPackIndex(Pack), Arg, TL.getNameLoc());
2678 }
2679 
2680 static concepts::Requirement::SubstitutionDiagnostic *
2681 createSubstDiag(Sema &S, TemplateDeductionInfo &Info,
2682  concepts::EntityPrinter Printer) {
2683  SmallString<128> Message;
2684  SourceLocation ErrorLoc;
2685  if (Info.hasSFINAEDiagnostic()) {
2686  PartialDiagnosticAt PDA(SourceLocation(),
2687  PartialDiagnostic::NullDiagnostic{});
2688  Info.takeSFINAEDiagnostic(PDA);
2689  PDA.second.EmitToString(S.getDiagnostics(), Message);
2690  ErrorLoc = PDA.first;
2691  } else {
2692  ErrorLoc = Info.getLocation();
2693  }
2694  char *MessageBuf = new (S.Context) char[Message.size()];
2695  std::copy(Message.begin(), Message.end(), MessageBuf);
2696  SmallString<128> Entity;
2697  llvm::raw_svector_ostream OS(Entity);
2698  Printer(OS);
2699  char *EntityBuf = new (S.Context) char[Entity.size()];
2700  std::copy(Entity.begin(), Entity.end(), EntityBuf);
2701  return new (S.Context) concepts::Requirement::SubstitutionDiagnostic{
2702  StringRef(EntityBuf, Entity.size()), ErrorLoc,
2703  StringRef(MessageBuf, Message.size())};
2704 }
2705 
2706 concepts::Requirement::SubstitutionDiagnostic *
2707 concepts::createSubstDiagAt(Sema &S, SourceLocation Location,
2708  EntityPrinter Printer) {
2709  SmallString<128> Entity;
2710  llvm::raw_svector_ostream OS(Entity);
2711  Printer(OS);
2712  char *EntityBuf = new (S.Context) char[Entity.size()];
2713  llvm::copy(Entity, EntityBuf);
2714  return new (S.Context) concepts::Requirement::SubstitutionDiagnostic{
2715  /*SubstitutedEntity=*/StringRef(EntityBuf, Entity.size()),
2716  /*DiagLoc=*/Location, /*DiagMessage=*/StringRef()};
2717 }
2718 
2719 ExprResult TemplateInstantiator::TransformRequiresTypeParams(
2720  SourceLocation KWLoc, SourceLocation RBraceLoc, const RequiresExpr *RE,
2721  RequiresExprBodyDecl *Body, ArrayRef<ParmVarDecl *> Params,
2722  SmallVectorImpl<QualType> &PTypes,
2723  SmallVectorImpl<ParmVarDecl *> &TransParams,
2724  Sema::ExtParameterInfoBuilder &PInfos) {
2725 
2726  TemplateDeductionInfo Info(KWLoc);
2727  Sema::InstantiatingTemplate TypeInst(SemaRef, KWLoc,
2728  RE, Info,
2729  SourceRange{KWLoc, RBraceLoc});
2730  Sema::SFINAETrap Trap(SemaRef);
2731 
2732  unsigned ErrorIdx;
2733  if (getDerived().TransformFunctionTypeParams(
2734  KWLoc, Params, /*ParamTypes=*/nullptr, /*ParamInfos=*/nullptr, PTypes,
2735  &TransParams, PInfos, &ErrorIdx) ||
2736  Trap.hasErrorOccurred()) {
2737  SmallVector<concepts::Requirement *, 4> TransReqs;
2738  ParmVarDecl *FailedDecl = Params[ErrorIdx];
2739  // Add a 'failed' Requirement to contain the error that caused the failure
2740  // here.
2741  TransReqs.push_back(RebuildTypeRequirement(createSubstDiag(
2742  SemaRef, Info, [&](llvm::raw_ostream &OS) { OS << *FailedDecl; })));
2743  return getDerived().RebuildRequiresExpr(KWLoc, Body, RE->getLParenLoc(),
2744  TransParams, RE->getRParenLoc(),
2745  TransReqs, RBraceLoc);
2746  }
2747 
2748  return ExprResult{};
2749 }
2750 
2751 concepts::TypeRequirement *
2752 TemplateInstantiator::TransformTypeRequirement(concepts::TypeRequirement *Req) {
2753  if (!Req->isDependent() && !AlwaysRebuild())
2754  return Req;
2755  if (Req->isSubstitutionFailure()) {
2756  if (AlwaysRebuild())
2757  return RebuildTypeRequirement(
2758  Req->getSubstitutionDiagnostic());
2759  return Req;
2760  }
2761 
2762  Sema::SFINAETrap Trap(SemaRef);
2763  TemplateDeductionInfo Info(Req->getType()->getTypeLoc().getBeginLoc());
2764  Sema::InstantiatingTemplate TypeInst(SemaRef,
2765  Req->getType()->getTypeLoc().getBeginLoc(), Req, Info,
2766  Req->getType()->getTypeLoc().getSourceRange());
2767  if (TypeInst.isInvalid())
2768  return nullptr;
2769  TypeSourceInfo *TransType = TransformType(Req->getType());
2770  if (!TransType || Trap.hasErrorOccurred())
2771  return RebuildTypeRequirement(createSubstDiag(SemaRef, Info,
2772  [&] (llvm::raw_ostream& OS) {
2773  Req->getType()->getType().print(OS, SemaRef.getPrintingPolicy());
2774  }));
2775  return RebuildTypeRequirement(TransType);
2776 }
2777 
2778 concepts::ExprRequirement *
2779 TemplateInstantiator::TransformExprRequirement(concepts::ExprRequirement *Req) {
2780  if (!Req->isDependent() && !AlwaysRebuild())
2781  return Req;
2782 
2783  Sema::SFINAETrap Trap(SemaRef);
2784 
2785  llvm::PointerUnion<Expr *, concepts::Requirement::SubstitutionDiagnostic *>
2786  TransExpr;
2787  if (Req->isExprSubstitutionFailure())
2788  TransExpr = Req->getExprSubstitutionDiagnostic();
2789  else {
2790  Expr *E = Req->getExpr();
2791  TemplateDeductionInfo Info(E->getBeginLoc());
2792  Sema::InstantiatingTemplate ExprInst(SemaRef, E->getBeginLoc(), Req, Info,
2793  E->getSourceRange());
2794  if (ExprInst.isInvalid())
2795  return nullptr;
2796  ExprResult TransExprRes = TransformExpr(E);
2797  if (!TransExprRes.isInvalid() && !Trap.hasErrorOccurred() &&
2798  TransExprRes.get()->hasPlaceholderType())
2799  TransExprRes = SemaRef.CheckPlaceholderExpr(TransExprRes.get());
2800  if (TransExprRes.isInvalid() || Trap.hasErrorOccurred())
2801  TransExpr = createSubstDiag(SemaRef, Info, [&](llvm::raw_ostream &OS) {
2802  E->printPretty(OS, nullptr, SemaRef.getPrintingPolicy());
2803  });
2804  else
2805  TransExpr = TransExprRes.get();
2806  }
2807 
2808  std::optional<concepts::ExprRequirement::ReturnTypeRequirement> TransRetReq;
2809  const auto &RetReq = Req->getReturnTypeRequirement();
2810  if (RetReq.isEmpty())
2811  TransRetReq.emplace();
2812  else if (RetReq.isSubstitutionFailure())
2813  TransRetReq.emplace(RetReq.getSubstitutionDiagnostic());
2814  else if (RetReq.isTypeConstraint()) {
2815  TemplateParameterList *OrigTPL =
2816  RetReq.getTypeConstraintTemplateParameterList();
2817  TemplateDeductionInfo Info(OrigTPL->getTemplateLoc());
2818  Sema::InstantiatingTemplate TPLInst(SemaRef, OrigTPL->getTemplateLoc(),
2819  Req, Info, OrigTPL->getSourceRange());
2820  if (TPLInst.isInvalid())
2821  return nullptr;
2822  TemplateParameterList *TPL = TransformTemplateParameterList(OrigTPL);
2823  if (!TPL)
2824  TransRetReq.emplace(createSubstDiag(SemaRef, Info,
2825  [&] (llvm::raw_ostream& OS) {
2826  RetReq.getTypeConstraint()->getImmediatelyDeclaredConstraint()
2827  ->printPretty(OS, nullptr, SemaRef.getPrintingPolicy());
2828  }));
2829  else {
2830  TPLInst.Clear();
2831  TransRetReq.emplace(TPL);
2832  }
2833  }
2834  assert(TransRetReq && "All code paths leading here must set TransRetReq");
2835  if (Expr *E = TransExpr.dyn_cast<Expr *>())
2836  return RebuildExprRequirement(E, Req->isSimple(), Req->getNoexceptLoc(),
2837  std::move(*TransRetReq));
2838  return RebuildExprRequirement(
2839  TransExpr.get<concepts::Requirement::SubstitutionDiagnostic *>(),
2840  Req->isSimple(), Req->getNoexceptLoc(), std::move(*TransRetReq));
2841 }
2842 
2843 concepts::NestedRequirement *
2844 TemplateInstantiator::TransformNestedRequirement(
2845  concepts::NestedRequirement *Req) {
2846  if (!Req->isDependent() && !AlwaysRebuild())
2847  return Req;
2848  if (Req->hasInvalidConstraint()) {
2849  if (AlwaysRebuild())
2850  return RebuildNestedRequirement(Req->getInvalidConstraintEntity(),
2851  Req->getConstraintSatisfaction());
2852  return Req;
2853  }
2854  Sema::InstantiatingTemplate ReqInst(SemaRef,
2855  Req->getConstraintExpr()->getBeginLoc(), Req,
2856  Sema::InstantiatingTemplate::ConstraintsCheck{},
2857  Req->getConstraintExpr()->getSourceRange());
2858  if (!getEvaluateConstraints()) {
2859  ExprResult TransConstraint = TransformExpr(Req->getConstraintExpr());
2860  if (TransConstraint.isInvalid() || !TransConstraint.get())
2861  return nullptr;
2862  if (TransConstraint.get()->isInstantiationDependent())
2863  return new (SemaRef.Context)
2864  concepts::NestedRequirement(TransConstraint.get());
2865  ConstraintSatisfaction Satisfaction;
2866  return new (SemaRef.Context) concepts::NestedRequirement(
2867  SemaRef.Context, TransConstraint.get(), Satisfaction);
2868  }
2869 
2870  ExprResult TransConstraint;
2871  ConstraintSatisfaction Satisfaction;
2872  TemplateDeductionInfo Info(Req->getConstraintExpr()->getBeginLoc());
2873  {
2874  EnterExpressionEvaluationContext ContextRAII(
2875  SemaRef, Sema::ExpressionEvaluationContext::ConstantEvaluated);
2876  Sema::SFINAETrap Trap(SemaRef);
2877  Sema::InstantiatingTemplate ConstrInst(SemaRef,
2878  Req->getConstraintExpr()->getBeginLoc(), Req, Info,
2879  Req->getConstraintExpr()->getSourceRange());
2880  if (ConstrInst.isInvalid())
2881  return nullptr;
2882  llvm::SmallVector<Expr *> Result;
2883  if (!SemaRef.CheckConstraintSatisfaction(
2884  nullptr, {Req->getConstraintExpr()}, Result, TemplateArgs,
2885  Req->getConstraintExpr()->getSourceRange(), Satisfaction) &&
2886  !Result.empty())
2887  TransConstraint = Result[0];
2888  assert(!Trap.hasErrorOccurred() && "Substitution failures must be handled "
2889  "by CheckConstraintSatisfaction.");
2890  }
2891  if (TransConstraint.isUsable() &&
2892  TransConstraint.get()->isInstantiationDependent())
2893  return new (SemaRef.Context)
2894  concepts::NestedRequirement(TransConstraint.get());
2895  if (TransConstraint.isInvalid() || !TransConstraint.get() ||
2896  Satisfaction.HasSubstitutionFailure()) {
2897  SmallString<128> Entity;
2898  llvm::raw_svector_ostream OS(Entity);
2899  Req->getConstraintExpr()->printPretty(OS, nullptr,
2900  SemaRef.getPrintingPolicy());
2901  char *EntityBuf = new (SemaRef.Context) char[Entity.size()];
2902  std::copy(Entity.begin(), Entity.end(), EntityBuf);
2903  return new (SemaRef.Context) concepts::NestedRequirement(
2904  SemaRef.Context, StringRef(EntityBuf, Entity.size()), Satisfaction);
2905  }
2906  return new (SemaRef.Context) concepts::NestedRequirement(
2907  SemaRef.Context, TransConstraint.get(), Satisfaction);
2908 }
2909 
2910 
2911 /// Perform substitution on the type T with a given set of template
2912 /// arguments.
2913 ///
2914 /// This routine substitutes the given template arguments into the
2915 /// type T and produces the instantiated type.
2916 ///
2917 /// \param T the type into which the template arguments will be
2918 /// substituted. If this type is not dependent, it will be returned
2919 /// immediately.
2920 ///
2921 /// \param Args the template arguments that will be
2922 /// substituted for the top-level template parameters within T.
2923 ///
2924 /// \param Loc the location in the source code where this substitution
2925 /// is being performed. It will typically be the location of the
2926 /// declarator (if we're instantiating the type of some declaration)
2927 /// or the location of the type in the source code (if, e.g., we're
2928 /// instantiating the type of a cast expression).
2929 ///
2930 /// \param Entity the name of the entity associated with a declaration
2931 /// being instantiated (if any). May be empty to indicate that there
2932 /// is no such entity (if, e.g., this is a type that occurs as part of
2933 /// a cast expression) or that the entity has no name (e.g., an
2934 /// unnamed function parameter).
2935 ///
2936 /// \param AllowDeducedTST Whether a DeducedTemplateSpecializationType is
2937 /// acceptable as the top level type of the result.
2938 ///
2939 /// \returns If the instantiation succeeds, the instantiated
2940 /// type. Otherwise, produces diagnostics and returns a NULL type.
2941 TypeSourceInfo *Sema::SubstType(TypeSourceInfo *T,
2942  const MultiLevelTemplateArgumentList &Args,
2943  SourceLocation Loc,
2944  DeclarationName Entity,
2945  bool AllowDeducedTST) {
2946  assert(!CodeSynthesisContexts.empty() &&
2947  "Cannot perform an instantiation without some context on the "
2948  "instantiation stack");
2949 
2950  if (!T->getType()->isInstantiationDependentType() &&
2951  !T->getType()->isVariablyModifiedType())
2952  return T;
2953 
2954  TemplateInstantiator Instantiator(*this, Args, Loc, Entity);
2955  return AllowDeducedTST ? Instantiator.TransformTypeWithDeducedTST(T)
2956  : Instantiator.TransformType(T);
2957 }
2958 
2959 TypeSourceInfo *Sema::SubstType(TypeLoc TL,
2960  const MultiLevelTemplateArgumentList &Args,
2961  SourceLocation Loc,
2962  DeclarationName Entity) {
2963  assert(!CodeSynthesisContexts.empty() &&
2964  "Cannot perform an instantiation without some context on the "
2965  "instantiation stack");
2966 
2967  if (TL.getType().isNull())
2968  return nullptr;
2969 
2970  if (!TL.getType()->isInstantiationDependentType() &&
2971  !TL.getType()->isVariablyModifiedType()) {
2972  // FIXME: Make a copy of the TypeLoc data here, so that we can
2973  // return a new TypeSourceInfo. Inefficient!
2974  TypeLocBuilder TLB;
2975  TLB.pushFullCopy(TL);
2976  return TLB.getTypeSourceInfo(Context, TL.getType());
2977  }
2978 
2979  TemplateInstantiator Instantiator(*this, Args, Loc, Entity);
2980  TypeLocBuilder TLB;
2981  TLB.reserve(TL.getFullDataSize());
2982  QualType Result = Instantiator.TransformType(TLB, TL);
2983  if (Result.isNull())
2984  return nullptr;
2985 
2986  return TLB.getTypeSourceInfo(Context, Result);
2987 }

2989 /// Deprecated form of the above.
2990 QualType Sema::SubstType(QualType T,
2991  const MultiLevelTemplateArgumentList &TemplateArgs,
2992  SourceLocation Loc, DeclarationName Entity) {
2993  assert(!CodeSynthesisContexts.empty() &&
2994  "Cannot perform an instantiation without some context on the "
2995  "instantiation stack");
2996 
2997  // If T is not a dependent type or a variably-modified type, there
2998  // is nothing to do.
2999  if (!T->isInstantiationDependentType() && !T->isVariablyModifiedType())
3000  return T;
3001 
3002  TemplateInstantiator Instantiator(*this, TemplateArgs, Loc, Entity);
3003  return Instantiator.TransformType(T);
3004 }

3006 static bool NeedsInstantiationAsFunctionType(TypeSourceInfo *T) {
3007  if (T->getType()->isInstantiationDependentType() ||
3008  T->getType()->isVariablyModifiedType())
3009  return true;
3010 
3011  TypeLoc TL = T->getTypeLoc().IgnoreParens();
3012  if (!TL.getAs<FunctionProtoTypeLoc>())
3013  return false;
3014 
3015  FunctionProtoTypeLoc FP = TL.castAs<FunctionProtoTypeLoc>();
3016  for (ParmVarDecl *P : FP.getParams()) {
3017  // This must be synthesized from a typedef.
3018  if (!P) continue;
3019 
3020  // If there are any parameters, a new TypeSourceInfo that refers to the
3021  // instantiated parameters must be built.
3022  return true;
3023  }
3024 
3025  return false;
3026 }
3027 
3028 /// A form of SubstType intended specifically for instantiating the
3029 /// type of a FunctionDecl. Its purpose is solely to force the
3030 /// instantiation of default-argument expressions and to avoid
3031 /// instantiating an exception-specification.
3032 TypeSourceInfo *Sema::SubstFunctionDeclType(TypeSourceInfo *T,
3033  const MultiLevelTemplateArgumentList &Args,
3034  SourceLocation Loc,
3035  DeclarationName Entity,
3036  CXXRecordDecl *ThisContext,
3037  Qualifiers ThisTypeQuals,
3038  bool EvaluateConstraints) {
3039  assert(!CodeSynthesisContexts.empty() &&
3040  "Cannot perform an instantiation without some context on the "
3041  "instantiation stack");
3042 
3043  if (!NeedsInstantiationAsFunctionType(T))
3044  return T;
3045 
3046  TemplateInstantiator Instantiator(*this, Args, Loc, Entity);
3047  Instantiator.setEvaluateConstraints(EvaluateConstraints);
3048 
3049  TypeLocBuilder TLB;
3050 
3051  TypeLoc TL = T->getTypeLoc();
3052  TLB.reserve(TL.getFullDataSize());
3053 
3054  QualType Result;
3055 
3056  if (FunctionProtoTypeLoc Proto =
3057  TL.IgnoreParens().getAs<FunctionProtoTypeLoc>()) {
3058  // Instantiate the type, other than its exception specification. The
3059  // exception specification is instantiated in InitFunctionInstantiation
3060  // once we've built the FunctionDecl.
3061  // FIXME: Set the exception specification to EST_Uninstantiated here,
3062  // instead of rebuilding the function type again later.
3063  Result = Instantiator.TransformFunctionProtoType(
3064  TLB, Proto, ThisContext, ThisTypeQuals,
3065  [](FunctionProtoType::ExceptionSpecInfo &ESI,
3066  bool &Changed) { return false; });
3067  } else {
3068  Result = Instantiator.TransformType(TLB, TL);
3069  }
3070  // When there are errors resolving types, clang may use IntTy as a fallback,
3071  // breaking our assumption that function declarations have function types.
3072  if (Result.isNull() || !Result->isFunctionType())
3073  return nullptr;
3074 
3075  return TLB.getTypeSourceInfo(Context, Result);
3076 }

3088 void Sema::SubstExceptionSpec(FunctionDecl *New, const FunctionProtoType *Proto,

3091  Proto->getExtProtoInfo().ExceptionSpec;

3094  if (SubstExceptionSpec(New->getTypeSourceInfo()->getTypeLoc().getEndLoc(),
3095  ESI, ExceptionStorage, Args))

3104  struct GetContainedInventedTypeParmVisitor :

3108  TemplateTypeParmDecl *>::Visit;
3109 
3110  TemplateTypeParmDecl *Visit(QualType T) {
3111  if (T.isNull())
3112  return nullptr;
3113  return Visit(T.getTypePtr());
3114  }
3115  // The deduced type itself.
3116  TemplateTypeParmDecl *VisitTemplateTypeParmType(
3117  const TemplateTypeParmType *T) {
3118  if (!T->getDecl() || !T->getDecl()->isImplicit())
3119  return nullptr;
3120  return T->getDecl();
3121  }

3124  // by references to invented parameters.

3141

3148  }
3149

3190 bool Sema::SubstTypeConstraint(
3191  TemplateTypeParmDecl *Inst, const TypeConstraint *TC,
3192  const MultiLevelTemplateArgumentList &TemplateArgs,
3193  bool EvaluateConstraints) {
3194  const ASTTemplateArgumentListInfo *TemplArgInfo =
3195  TC->getTemplateArgsAsWritten();
3196 
3197  if (!EvaluateConstraints) {
3198  Inst->setTypeConstraint(TC->getConceptReference(),
3199  TC->getImmediatelyDeclaredConstraint());
3200  return false;
3201  }
3202 
3203  TemplateArgumentListInfo InstArgs;
3204 
3205  if (TemplArgInfo) {
3206  InstArgs.setLAngleLoc(TemplArgInfo->LAngleLoc);
3207  InstArgs.setRAngleLoc(TemplArgInfo->RAngleLoc);
3208  if (SubstTemplateArguments(TemplArgInfo->arguments(), TemplateArgs,
3209  InstArgs))
3210  return true;
3211  }
3212  return AttachTypeConstraint(
3213  TC->getNestedNameSpecifierLoc(), TC->getConceptNameInfo(),
3214  TC->getNamedConcept(),
3215  /*FoundDecl=*/TC->getConceptReference()->getFoundDecl(), &InstArgs, Inst,
3216  Inst->isParameterPack()
3217  ? cast<CXXFoldExpr>(TC->getImmediatelyDeclaredConstraint())
3218  ->getEllipsisLoc()
3219  : SourceLocation());
3220 }
3221 
3222 ParmVarDecl *Sema::SubstParmVarDecl(
3223  ParmVarDecl *OldParm, const MultiLevelTemplateArgumentList &TemplateArgs,
3224  int indexAdjustment, std::optional<unsigned> NumExpansions,
3225  bool ExpectParameterPack, bool EvaluateConstraint) {
3226  TypeSourceInfo *OldDI = OldParm->getTypeSourceInfo();
3227  TypeSourceInfo *NewDI = nullptr;
3228 
3229  TypeLoc OldTL = OldDI->getTypeLoc();
3230  if (PackExpansionTypeLoc ExpansionTL = OldTL.getAs<PackExpansionTypeLoc>()) {
3231 
3232  // We have a function parameter pack. Substitute into the pattern of the
3233  // expansion.
3234  NewDI = SubstType(ExpansionTL.getPatternLoc(), TemplateArgs,
3235  OldParm->getLocation(), OldParm->getDeclName());
3236  if (!NewDI)
3237  return nullptr;
3238 
3239  if (NewDI->getType()->containsUnexpandedParameterPack()) {
3240  // We still have unexpanded parameter packs, which means that
3241  // our function parameter is still a function parameter pack.
3242  // Therefore, make its type a pack expansion type.
3243  NewDI = CheckPackExpansion(NewDI, ExpansionTL.getEllipsisLoc(),
3244  NumExpansions);
3245  } else if (ExpectParameterPack) {
3246  // We expected to get a parameter pack but didn't (because the type
3247  // itself is not a pack expansion type), so complain. This can occur when
3248  // the substitution goes through an alias template that "loses" the
3249  // pack expansion.
3250  Diag(OldParm->getLocation(),
3251  diag::err_function_parameter_pack_without_parameter_packs)
3252  << NewDI->getType();
3253  return nullptr;
3254  }
3255  } else {
3256  NewDI = SubstType(OldDI, TemplateArgs, OldParm->getLocation(),
3257  OldParm->getDeclName());
3258  }
3259 
3260  if (!NewDI)
3261  return nullptr;
3262 
3263  if (NewDI->getType()->isVoidType()) {
3264  Diag(OldParm->getLocation(), diag::err_param_with_void_type);
3265  return nullptr;
3266  }
3267 
3268  // In abbreviated templates, TemplateTypeParmDecls with possible
3269  // TypeConstraints are created when the parameter list is originally parsed.
3270  // The TypeConstraints can therefore reference other functions parameters in
3271  // the abbreviated function template, which is why we must instantiate them
3272  // here, when the instantiated versions of those referenced parameters are in
3273  // scope.
3274  if (TemplateTypeParmDecl *TTP =
3275  GetContainedInventedTypeParmVisitor().Visit(OldDI->getType())) {
3276  if (const TypeConstraint *TC = TTP->getTypeConstraint()) {
3277  auto *Inst = cast_or_null<TemplateTypeParmDecl>(
3278  FindInstantiatedDecl(TTP->getLocation(), TTP, TemplateArgs));
3279  // We will first get here when instantiating the abbreviated function
3280  // template's described function, but we might also get here later.
3281  // Make sure we do not instantiate the TypeConstraint more than once.
3282  if (Inst && !Inst->getTypeConstraint()) {
3283  if (SubstTypeConstraint(Inst, TC, TemplateArgs, EvaluateConstraint))
3284  return nullptr;
3285  }
3286  }
3287  }
3288 
3289  ParmVarDecl *NewParm = CheckParameter(Context.getTranslationUnitDecl(),
3290  OldParm->getInnerLocStart(),
3291  OldParm->getLocation(),
3292  OldParm->getIdentifier(),
3293  NewDI->getType(), NewDI,
3294  OldParm->getStorageClass());
3295  if (!NewParm)
3296  return nullptr;
3297 
3298  // Mark the (new) default argument as uninstantiated (if any).
3299  if (OldParm->hasUninstantiatedDefaultArg()) {
3300  Expr *Arg = OldParm->getUninstantiatedDefaultArg();
3301  NewParm->setUninstantiatedDefaultArg(Arg);
3302  } else if (OldParm->hasUnparsedDefaultArg()) {
3303  NewParm->setUnparsedDefaultArg();
3304  UnparsedDefaultArgInstantiations[OldParm].push_back(NewParm);
3305  } else if (Expr *Arg = OldParm->getDefaultArg()) {
3306  // Default arguments cannot be substituted until the declaration context
3307  // for the associated function or lambda capture class is available.
3308  // This is necessary for cases like the following where construction of
3309  // the lambda capture class for the outer lambda is dependent on the
3310  // parameter types but where the default argument is dependent on the
3311  // outer lambda's declaration context.
3312  // template <typename T>
3313  // auto f() {
3314  // return [](T = []{ return T{}; }()) { return 0; };
3315  // }
3316  NewParm->setUninstantiatedDefaultArg(Arg);
3317  }
3318 
3319  NewParm->setExplicitObjectParameterLoc(
3320  OldParm->getExplicitObjectParamThisLoc());
3321  NewParm->setHasInheritedDefaultArg(OldParm->hasInheritedDefaultArg());
3322 
3323  if (OldParm->isParameterPack() && !NewParm->isParameterPack()) {
3324  // Add the new parameter to the instantiated parameter pack.
3325  CurrentInstantiationScope->InstantiatedLocalPackArg(OldParm, NewParm);
3326  } else {
3327  // Introduce an Old -> New mapping
3328  CurrentInstantiationScope->InstantiatedLocal(OldParm, NewParm);
3329  }
3330 
3331  // FIXME: OldParm may come from a FunctionProtoType, in which case CurContext
3332  // can be anything, is this right ?
3333  NewParm->setDeclContext(CurContext);
3334 
3335  NewParm->setScopeInfo(OldParm->getFunctionScopeDepth(),
3336  OldParm->getFunctionScopeIndex() + indexAdjustment);
3337 
3338  InstantiateAttrs(TemplateArgs, OldParm, NewParm);
3339 
3340  return NewParm;
3341 }

3346 bool Sema::SubstParmTypes(
3347  SourceLocation Loc, ArrayRef<ParmVarDecl *> Params,
3348  const FunctionProtoType::ExtParameterInfo *ExtParamInfos,
3349  const MultiLevelTemplateArgumentList &TemplateArgs,

3351  SmallVectorImpl<ParmVarDecl *> *OutParams,
3352  ExtParameterInfoBuilder &ParamInfos) {
3353  assert(!CodeSynthesisContexts.empty() &&
3354  "Cannot perform an instantiation without some context on the "
3355  "instantiation stack");
3356 
3357  TemplateInstantiator Instantiator(*this, TemplateArgs, Loc,

3363 /// Substitute the given template arguments into the default argument.
3364 bool Sema::SubstDefaultArgument(
3365  SourceLocation Loc,
3366  ParmVarDecl *Param,
3367  const MultiLevelTemplateArgumentList &TemplateArgs,
3368  bool ForCallExpr) {
3369  FunctionDecl *FD = cast<FunctionDecl>(Param->getDeclContext());
3370  Expr *PatternExpr = Param->getUninstantiatedDefaultArg();
3371 
3372  EnterExpressionEvaluationContext EvalContext(
3373  *this, ExpressionEvaluationContext::PotentiallyEvaluated, Param);
3374 
3375  InstantiatingTemplate Inst(*this, Loc, Param, TemplateArgs.getInnermost());
3376  if (Inst.isInvalid())
3377  return true;
3378  if (Inst.isAlreadyInstantiating()) {
3379  Diag(Param->getBeginLoc(), diag::err_recursive_default_argument) << FD;
3380  Param->setInvalidDecl();
3381  return true;
3382  }
3383 
3384  ExprResult Result;
3385  {
3386  // C++ [dcl.fct.default]p5:
3387  // The names in the [default argument] expression are bound, and
3388  // the semantic constraints are checked, at the point where the
3389  // default argument expression appears.
3390  ContextRAII SavedContext(*this, FD);
3391  std::unique_ptr<LocalInstantiationScope> LIS;
3392  MultiLevelTemplateArgumentList NewTemplateArgs = TemplateArgs;
3393 
3394  if (ForCallExpr) {
3395  // When instantiating a default argument due to use in a call expression,
3396  // an instantiation scope that includes the parameters of the callee is
3397  // required to satisfy references from the default argument. For example:
3398  // template<typename T> void f(T a, int = decltype(a)());
3399  // void g() { f(0); }
3400  LIS = std::make_unique<LocalInstantiationScope>(*this);
3401  FunctionDecl *PatternFD = FD->getTemplateInstantiationPattern(
3402  /*ForDefinition*/ false);
3403  if (addInstantiatedParametersToScope(FD, PatternFD, *LIS, TemplateArgs))
3404  return true;
3405  const FunctionTemplateDecl *PrimaryTemplate = FD->getPrimaryTemplate();
3406  if (PrimaryTemplate && PrimaryTemplate->isOutOfLine()) {
3407  TemplateArgumentList *CurrentTemplateArgumentList =
3408  TemplateArgumentList::CreateCopy(getASTContext(),
3409  TemplateArgs.getInnermost());
3410  NewTemplateArgs = getTemplateInstantiationArgs(
3411  FD, FD->getDeclContext(), /*Final=*/false,
3412  CurrentTemplateArgumentList->asArray(), /*RelativeToPrimary=*/true);
3413  }
3414  }
3415 
3416  runWithSufficientStackSpace(Loc, [&] {
3417  Result = SubstInitializer(PatternExpr, NewTemplateArgs,
3418  /*DirectInit*/ false);
3419  });
3420  }
3421  if (Result.isInvalid())
3422  return true;
3423 
3424  if (ForCallExpr) {
3425  // Check the expression as an initializer for the parameter.
3426  InitializedEntity Entity
3427  = InitializedEntity::InitializeParameter(Context, Param);
3428  InitializationKind Kind = InitializationKind::CreateCopy(
3429  Param->getLocation(),
3430  /*FIXME:EqualLoc*/ PatternExpr->getBeginLoc());
3431  Expr *ResultE = Result.getAs<Expr>();
3432 
3433  InitializationSequence InitSeq(*this, Entity, Kind, ResultE);
3434  Result = InitSeq.Perform(*this, Entity, Kind, ResultE);
3435  if (Result.isInvalid())
3436  return true;
3437 
3438  Result =
3439  ActOnFinishFullExpr(Result.getAs<Expr>(), Param->getOuterLocStart(),
3440  /*DiscardedValue*/ false);
3441  } else {
3442  // FIXME: Obtain the source location for the '=' token.
3443  SourceLocation EqualLoc = PatternExpr->getBeginLoc();
3444  Result = ConvertParamDefaultArgument(Param, Result.getAs<Expr>(), EqualLoc);
3445  }
3446  if (Result.isInvalid())
3447  return true;
3448 
3449  // Remember the instantiated default argument.
3450  Param->setDefaultArg(Result.getAs<Expr>());
3451 
3452  return false;
3453 }
3454 
3455 /// Perform substitution on the base class specifiers of the
3456 /// given class template specialization.
3457 ///
3458 /// Produces a diagnostic and returns true on error, returns false and
3459 /// attaches the instantiated base classes to the class template
3460 /// specialization if successful.
3461 bool
3462 Sema::SubstBaseSpecifiers(CXXRecordDecl *Instantiation,
3463  CXXRecordDecl *Pattern,
3464  const MultiLevelTemplateArgumentList &TemplateArgs) {
3465  bool Invalid = false;
3466  SmallVector<CXXBaseSpecifier*, 4> InstantiatedBases;
3467  for (const auto &Base : Pattern->bases()) {
3468  if (!Base.getType()->isDependentType()) {
3469  if (const CXXRecordDecl *RD = Base.getType()->getAsCXXRecordDecl()) {
3470  if (RD->isInvalidDecl())
3471  Instantiation->setInvalidDecl();
3472  }
3473  InstantiatedBases.push_back(new (Context) CXXBaseSpecifier(Base));
3474  continue;
3475  }
3476 
3477  SourceLocation EllipsisLoc;
3478  TypeSourceInfo *BaseTypeLoc;
3479  if (Base.isPackExpansion()) {
3480  // This is a pack expansion. See whether we should expand it now, or
3481  // wait until later.
3482  SmallVector<UnexpandedParameterPack, 2> Unexpanded;
3483  collectUnexpandedParameterPacks(Base.getTypeSourceInfo()->getTypeLoc(),
3484  Unexpanded);
3485  bool ShouldExpand = false;
3486  bool RetainExpansion = false;
3487  std::optional<unsigned> NumExpansions;
3488  if (CheckParameterPacksForExpansion(Base.getEllipsisLoc(),
3489  Base.getSourceRange(),
3490  Unexpanded,
3491  TemplateArgs, ShouldExpand,
3492  RetainExpansion,
3493  NumExpansions)) {
3494  Invalid = true;
3495  continue;
3496  }
3497 
3498  // If we should expand this pack expansion now, do so.
3499  if (ShouldExpand) {
3500  for (unsigned I = 0; I != *NumExpansions; ++I) {
3501  Sema::ArgumentPackSubstitutionIndexRAII SubstIndex(*this, I);
3502 
3503  TypeSourceInfo *BaseTypeLoc = SubstType(Base.getTypeSourceInfo(),
3504  TemplateArgs,
3505  Base.getSourceRange().getBegin(),
3506  DeclarationName());
3507  if (!BaseTypeLoc) {
3508  Invalid = true;
3509  continue;
3510  }
3511 
3512  if (CXXBaseSpecifier *InstantiatedBase
3513  = CheckBaseSpecifier(Instantiation,
3514  Base.getSourceRange(),
3515  Base.isVirtual(),
3516  Base.getAccessSpecifierAsWritten(),
3517  BaseTypeLoc,
3518  SourceLocation()))
3519  InstantiatedBases.push_back(InstantiatedBase);
3520  else
3521  Invalid = true;
3522  }
3523 
3524  continue;
3525  }
3526 
3527  // The resulting base specifier will (still) be a pack expansion.
3528  EllipsisLoc = Base.getEllipsisLoc();
3529  Sema::ArgumentPackSubstitutionIndexRAII SubstIndex(*this, -1);
3530  BaseTypeLoc = SubstType(Base.getTypeSourceInfo(),
3531  TemplateArgs,
3532  Base.getSourceRange().getBegin(),
3533  DeclarationName());
3534  } else {
3535  BaseTypeLoc = SubstType(Base.getTypeSourceInfo(),
3536  TemplateArgs,
3537  Base.getSourceRange().getBegin(),
3538  DeclarationName());
3539  }
3540 
3541  if (!BaseTypeLoc) {
3542  Invalid = true;
3543  continue;
3544  }
3545 
3546  if (CXXBaseSpecifier *InstantiatedBase
3547  = CheckBaseSpecifier(Instantiation,
3548  Base.getSourceRange(),
3549  Base.isVirtual(),
3550  Base.getAccessSpecifierAsWritten(),
3551  BaseTypeLoc,
3552  EllipsisLoc))
3553  InstantiatedBases.push_back(InstantiatedBase);
3554  else
3555  Invalid = true;
3556  }
3557 
3558  if (!Invalid && AttachBaseSpecifiers(Instantiation, InstantiatedBases))
3559  Invalid = true;
3560 
3561  return Invalid;
3562 }
3563 
3564 // Defined via #include from SemaTemplateInstantiateDecl.cpp
3565 namespace clang {
3566  namespace sema {
3567  Attr *instantiateTemplateAttribute(const Attr *At, ASTContext &C, Sema &S,
3568  const MultiLevelTemplateArgumentList &TemplateArgs);
3569  Attr *instantiateTemplateAttributeForDecl(
3570  const Attr *At, ASTContext &C, Sema &S,
3571  const MultiLevelTemplateArgumentList &TemplateArgs);
3572  }
3573 }
3574 
3575 /// Instantiate the definition of a class from a given pattern.
3576 ///
3577 /// \param PointOfInstantiation The point of instantiation within the
3578 /// source code.
3579 ///
3580 /// \param Instantiation is the declaration whose definition is being
3581 /// instantiated. This will be either a class template specialization
3582 /// or a member class of a class template specialization.
3583 ///
3584 /// \param Pattern is the pattern from which the instantiation
3585 /// occurs. This will be either the declaration of a class template or
3586 /// the declaration of a member class of a class template.
3587 ///
3588 /// \param TemplateArgs The template arguments to be substituted into
3589 /// the pattern.
3590 ///
3591 /// \param TSK the kind of implicit or explicit instantiation to perform.
3592 ///
3593 /// \param Complain whether to complain if the class cannot be instantiated due
3594 /// to the lack of a definition.
3595 ///
3596 /// \returns true if an error occurred, false otherwise.
3597 bool
3598 Sema::InstantiateClass(SourceLocation PointOfInstantiation,
3599  CXXRecordDecl *Instantiation, CXXRecordDecl *Pattern,
3600  const MultiLevelTemplateArgumentList &TemplateArgs,
3601  TemplateSpecializationKind TSK,
3602  bool Complain) {
3603  CXXRecordDecl *PatternDef
3604  = cast_or_null<CXXRecordDecl>(Pattern->getDefinition());
3605  if (DiagnoseUninstantiableTemplate(PointOfInstantiation, Instantiation,
3606  Instantiation->getInstantiatedFromMemberClass(),
3607  Pattern, PatternDef, TSK, Complain))
3608  return true;
3609 
3610  llvm::TimeTraceScope TimeScope("InstantiateClass", [&]() {
3611  std::string Name;
3612  llvm::raw_string_ostream OS(Name);
3613  Instantiation->getNameForDiagnostic(OS, getPrintingPolicy(),
3614  /*Qualified=*/true);
3615  return Name;
3616  });
3617 
3618  Pattern = PatternDef;
3619 
3620  // Record the point of instantiation.
3621  if (MemberSpecializationInfo *MSInfo
3622  = Instantiation->getMemberSpecializationInfo()) {
3623  MSInfo->setTemplateSpecializationKind(TSK);
3624  MSInfo->setPointOfInstantiation(PointOfInstantiation);
3625  } else if (ClassTemplateSpecializationDecl *Spec
3626  = dyn_cast<ClassTemplateSpecializationDecl>(Instantiation)) {
3627  Spec->setTemplateSpecializationKind(TSK);
3628  Spec->setPointOfInstantiation(PointOfInstantiation);
3629  }
3630 
3631  InstantiatingTemplate Inst(*this, PointOfInstantiation, Instantiation);
3632  if (Inst.isInvalid())
3633  return true;
3634  assert(!Inst.isAlreadyInstantiating() && "should have been caught by caller");
3635  PrettyDeclStackTraceEntry CrashInfo(Context, Instantiation, SourceLocation(),
3636  "instantiating class definition");
3637 
3638  // Enter the scope of this instantiation. We don't use
3639  // PushDeclContext because we don't have a scope.
3640  ContextRAII SavedContext(*this, Instantiation);
3641  EnterExpressionEvaluationContext EvalContext(
3642  *this, Sema::ExpressionEvaluationContext::PotentiallyEvaluated);
3643 
3644  // If this is an instantiation of a local class, merge this local
3645  // instantiation scope with the enclosing scope. Otherwise, every
3646  // instantiation of a class has its own local instantiation scope.
3647  bool MergeWithParentScope = !Instantiation->isDefinedOutsideFunctionOrMethod();
3648  LocalInstantiationScope Scope(*this, MergeWithParentScope);
3649 
3650  // Some class state isn't processed immediately but delayed till class
3651  // instantiation completes. We may not be ready to handle any delayed state
3652  // already on the stack as it might correspond to a different class, so save
3653  // it now and put it back later.
3654  SavePendingParsedClassStateRAII SavedPendingParsedClassState(*this);
3655 
3656  // Pull attributes from the pattern onto the instantiation.
3657  InstantiateAttrs(TemplateArgs, Pattern, Instantiation);
3658 
3659  // Start the definition of this instantiation.
3660  Instantiation->startDefinition();
3661 
3662  // The instantiation is visible here, even if it was first declared in an
3663  // unimported module.
3664  Instantiation->setVisibleDespiteOwningModule();
3665 
3666  // FIXME: This loses the as-written tag kind for an explicit instantiation.
3667  Instantiation->setTagKind(Pattern->getTagKind());
3668 
3669  // Do substitution on the base class specifiers.
3670  if (SubstBaseSpecifiers(Instantiation, Pattern, TemplateArgs))
3671  Instantiation->setInvalidDecl();
3672 
3673  TemplateDeclInstantiator Instantiator(*this, Instantiation, TemplateArgs);
3674  Instantiator.setEvaluateConstraints(false);
3675  SmallVector<Decl*, 4> Fields;
3676  // Delay instantiation of late parsed attributes.
3677  LateInstantiatedAttrVec LateAttrs;
3678  Instantiator.enableLateAttributeInstantiation(&LateAttrs);
3679 
3680  bool MightHaveConstexprVirtualFunctions = false;
3681  for (auto *Member : Pattern->decls()) {
3682  // Don't instantiate members not belonging in this semantic context.
3683  // e.g. for:
3684  // @code
3685  // template <int i> class A {
3686  // class B *g;
3687  // };
3688  // @endcode
3689  // 'class B' has the template as lexical context but semantically it is
3690  // introduced in namespace scope.
3691  if (Member->getDeclContext() != Pattern)
3692  continue;
3693 
3694  // BlockDecls can appear in a default-member-initializer. They must be the
3695  // child of a BlockExpr, so we only know how to instantiate them from there.
3696  // Similarly, lambda closure types are recreated when instantiating the
3697  // corresponding LambdaExpr.
3698  if (isa<BlockDecl>(Member) ||
3699  (isa<CXXRecordDecl>(Member) && cast<CXXRecordDecl>(Member)->isLambda()))
3700  continue;
3701 
3702  if (Member->isInvalidDecl()) {
3703  Instantiation->setInvalidDecl();
3704  continue;
3705  }
3706 
3707  Decl *NewMember = Instantiator.Visit(Member);
3708  if (NewMember) {
3709  if (FieldDecl *Field = dyn_cast<FieldDecl>(NewMember)) {
3710  Fields.push_back(Field);
3711  } else if (EnumDecl *Enum = dyn_cast<EnumDecl>(NewMember)) {
3712  // C++11 [temp.inst]p1: The implicit instantiation of a class template
3713  // specialization causes the implicit instantiation of the definitions
3714  // of unscoped member enumerations.
3715  // Record a point of instantiation for this implicit instantiation.
3716  if (TSK == TSK_ImplicitInstantiation && !Enum->isScoped() &&
3717  Enum->isCompleteDefinition()) {
3718  MemberSpecializationInfo *MSInfo =Enum->getMemberSpecializationInfo();
3719  assert(MSInfo && "no spec info for member enum specialization");
3720  MSInfo->setTemplateSpecializationKind(TSK_ImplicitInstantiation);
3721  MSInfo->setPointOfInstantiation(PointOfInstantiation);
3722  }
3723  } else if (StaticAssertDecl *SA = dyn_cast<StaticAssertDecl>(NewMember)) {
3724  if (SA->isFailed()) {
3725  // A static_assert failed. Bail out; instantiating this
3726  // class is probably not meaningful.
3727  Instantiation->setInvalidDecl();
3728  break;
3729  }
3730  } else if (CXXMethodDecl *MD = dyn_cast<CXXMethodDecl>(NewMember)) {
3731  if (MD->isConstexpr() && !MD->getFriendObjectKind() &&
3732  (MD->isVirtualAsWritten() || Instantiation->getNumBases()))
3733  MightHaveConstexprVirtualFunctions = true;
3734  }
3735 
3736  if (NewMember->isInvalidDecl())
3737  Instantiation->setInvalidDecl();
3738  } else {
3739  // FIXME: Eventually, a NULL return will mean that one of the
3740  // instantiations was a semantic disaster, and we'll want to mark the
3741  // declaration invalid.
3742  // For now, we expect to skip some members that we can't yet handle.
3743  }
3744  }
3745 
3746  // Finish checking fields.
3747  ActOnFields(nullptr, Instantiation->getLocation(), Instantiation, Fields,
3748  SourceLocation(), SourceLocation(), ParsedAttributesView());
3749  CheckCompletedCXXClass(nullptr, Instantiation);
3750 
3751  // Default arguments are parsed, if not instantiated. We can go instantiate
3752  // default arg exprs for default constructors if necessary now. Unless we're
3753  // parsing a class, in which case wait until that's finished.
3754  if (ParsingClassDepth == 0)
3755  ActOnFinishCXXNonNestedClass();
3756 
3757  // Instantiate late parsed attributes, and attach them to their decls.
3758  // See Sema::InstantiateAttrs
3759  for (LateInstantiatedAttrVec::iterator I = LateAttrs.begin(),
3760  E = LateAttrs.end(); I != E; ++I) {
3761  assert(CurrentInstantiationScope == Instantiator.getStartingScope());
3762  CurrentInstantiationScope = I->Scope;
3763 
3764  // Allow 'this' within late-parsed attributes.
3765  auto *ND = cast<NamedDecl>(I->NewDecl);
3766  auto *ThisContext = dyn_cast_or_null<CXXRecordDecl>(ND->getDeclContext());
3767  CXXThisScopeRAII ThisScope(*this, ThisContext, Qualifiers(),
3768  ND->isCXXInstanceMember());
3769 
3770  Attr *NewAttr =
3771  instantiateTemplateAttribute(I->TmplAttr, Context, *this, TemplateArgs);
3772  if (NewAttr)
3773  I->NewDecl->addAttr(NewAttr);
3774  LocalInstantiationScope::deleteScopes(I->Scope,
3775  Instantiator.getStartingScope());
3776  }
3777  Instantiator.disableLateAttributeInstantiation();
3778  LateAttrs.clear();
3779 
3780  ActOnFinishDelayedMemberInitializers(Instantiation);
3781 
3782  // FIXME: We should do something similar for explicit instantiations so they
3783  // end up in the right module.
3784  if (TSK == TSK_ImplicitInstantiation) {
3785  Instantiation->setLocation(Pattern->getLocation());
3786  Instantiation->setLocStart(Pattern->getInnerLocStart());
3787  Instantiation->setBraceRange(Pattern->getBraceRange());
3788  }
3789 
3790  if (!Instantiation->isInvalidDecl()) {
3791  // Perform any dependent diagnostics from the pattern.
3792  if (Pattern->isDependentContext())
3793  PerformDependentDiagnostics(Pattern, TemplateArgs);
3794 
3795  // Instantiate any out-of-line class template partial
3796  // specializations now.
3797  for (TemplateDeclInstantiator::delayed_partial_spec_iterator
3798  P = Instantiator.delayed_partial_spec_begin(),
3799  PEnd = Instantiator.delayed_partial_spec_end();
3800  P != PEnd; ++P) {
3801  if (!Instantiator.InstantiateClassTemplatePartialSpecialization(
3802  P->first, P->second)) {
3803  Instantiation->setInvalidDecl();
3804  break;
3805  }
3806  }
3807 
3808  // Instantiate any out-of-line variable template partial
3809  // specializations now.
3810  for (TemplateDeclInstantiator::delayed_var_partial_spec_iterator
3811  P = Instantiator.delayed_var_partial_spec_begin(),
3812  PEnd = Instantiator.delayed_var_partial_spec_end();
3813  P != PEnd; ++P) {
3814  if (!Instantiator.InstantiateVarTemplatePartialSpecialization(
3815  P->first, P->second)) {
3816  Instantiation->setInvalidDecl();
3817  break;
3818  }
3819  }
3820  }
3821 
3822  // Exit the scope of this instantiation.
3823  SavedContext.pop();
3824 
3825  if (!Instantiation->isInvalidDecl()) {
3826  // Always emit the vtable for an explicit instantiation definition
3827  // of a polymorphic class template specialization. Otherwise, eagerly
3828  // instantiate only constexpr virtual functions in preparation for their use
3829  // in constant evaluation.
3830  if (TSK == TSK_ExplicitInstantiationDefinition)
3831  MarkVTableUsed(PointOfInstantiation, Instantiation, true);
3832  else if (MightHaveConstexprVirtualFunctions)
3833  MarkVirtualMembersReferenced(PointOfInstantiation, Instantiation,
3834  /*ConstexprOnly*/ true);
3835  }
3836 
3837  Consumer.HandleTagDeclDefinition(Instantiation);
3838 
3839  return Instantiation->isInvalidDecl();
3840 }
3841 
3842 /// Instantiate the definition of an enum from a given pattern.
3843 ///
3844 /// \param PointOfInstantiation The point of instantiation within the
3845 /// source code.
3846 /// \param Instantiation is the declaration whose definition is being
3847 /// instantiated. This will be a member enumeration of a class
3848 /// temploid specialization, or a local enumeration within a
3849 /// function temploid specialization.
3850 /// \param Pattern The templated declaration from which the instantiation
3851 /// occurs.
3852 /// \param TemplateArgs The template arguments to be substituted into
3853 /// the pattern.
3854 /// \param TSK The kind of implicit or explicit instantiation to perform.
3855 ///
3856 /// \return \c true if an error occurred, \c false otherwise.
3857 bool Sema::InstantiateEnum(SourceLocation PointOfInstantiation,
3858  EnumDecl *Instantiation, EnumDecl *Pattern,
3859  const MultiLevelTemplateArgumentList &TemplateArgs,
3860  TemplateSpecializationKind TSK) {
3861  EnumDecl *PatternDef = Pattern->getDefinition();
3862  if (DiagnoseUninstantiableTemplate(PointOfInstantiation, Instantiation,
3863  Instantiation->getInstantiatedFromMemberEnum(),
3864  Pattern, PatternDef, TSK,/*Complain*/true))
3865  return true;
3866  Pattern = PatternDef;
3867 
3868  // Record the point of instantiation.
3869  if (MemberSpecializationInfo *MSInfo
3870  = Instantiation->getMemberSpecializationInfo()) {
3871  MSInfo->setTemplateSpecializationKind(TSK);
3872  MSInfo->setPointOfInstantiation(PointOfInstantiation);
3873  }
3874 
3875  InstantiatingTemplate Inst(*this, PointOfInstantiation, Instantiation);
3876  if (Inst.isInvalid())
3877  return true;
3878  if (Inst.isAlreadyInstantiating())
3879  return false;
3880  PrettyDeclStackTraceEntry CrashInfo(Context, Instantiation, SourceLocation(),
3881  "instantiating enum definition");
3882 
3883  // The instantiation is visible here, even if it was first declared in an
3884  // unimported module.
3885  Instantiation->setVisibleDespiteOwningModule();
3886 
3887  // Enter the scope of this instantiation. We don't use
3888  // PushDeclContext because we don't have a scope.
3889  ContextRAII SavedContext(*this, Instantiation);
3890  EnterExpressionEvaluationContext EvalContext(
3891  *this, Sema::ExpressionEvaluationContext::PotentiallyEvaluated);
3892 
3893  LocalInstantiationScope Scope(*this, /*MergeWithParentScope*/true);
3894 
3895  // Pull attributes from the pattern onto the instantiation.
3896  InstantiateAttrs(TemplateArgs, Pattern, Instantiation);
3897 
3898  TemplateDeclInstantiator Instantiator(*this, Instantiation, TemplateArgs);
3899  Instantiator.InstantiateEnumDefinition(Instantiation, Pattern);
3900 
3901  // Exit the scope of this instantiation.
3902  SavedContext.pop();
3903 
3904  return Instantiation->isInvalidDecl();
3905 }

3908 /// Instantiate the definition of a field from the given pattern.
3909 ///
3910 /// \param PointOfInstantiation The point of instantiation within the
3911 /// source code.
3912 /// \param Instantiation is the declaration whose definition is being
3913 /// instantiated. This will be a class of a class temploid
3914 /// specialization, or a local enumeration within a function temploid
3915 /// specialization.
3916 /// \param Pattern The templated declaration from which the instantiation
3917 /// occurs.
3918 /// \param TemplateArgs The template arguments to be substituted into
3919 /// the pattern.
3920 ///
3921 /// \return \c true if an error occurred, \c false otherwise.
3922 bool Sema::InstantiateInClassInitializer(
3923  SourceLocation PointOfInstantiation, FieldDecl *Instantiation,
3924  FieldDecl *Pattern, const MultiLevelTemplateArgumentList &TemplateArgs) {
3925  // If there is no initializer, we don't need to do anything.
3926  if (!Pattern->hasInClassInitializer())
3927  return false;
3928 
3929  assert(Instantiation->getInClassInitStyle() ==
3930  Pattern->getInClassInitStyle() &&
3931  "pattern and instantiation disagree about init style");
3932 
3933  // Error out if we haven't parsed the initializer of the pattern yet because
3934  // we are waiting for the closing brace of the outer class.
3935  Expr *OldInit = Pattern->getInClassInitializer();
3936  if (!OldInit) {
3937  RecordDecl *PatternRD = Pattern->getParent();
3938  RecordDecl *OutermostClass = PatternRD->getOuterLexicalRecordContext();
3939  Diag(PointOfInstantiation,
3940  diag::err_default_member_initializer_not_yet_parsed)
3941  << OutermostClass << Pattern;
3942  Diag(Pattern->getEndLoc(),
3943  diag::note_default_member_initializer_not_yet_parsed);
3944  Instantiation->setInvalidDecl();
3945  return true;
3946  }
3947 
3948  InstantiatingTemplate Inst(*this, PointOfInstantiation, Instantiation);
3949  if (Inst.isInvalid())
3950  return true;
3951  if (Inst.isAlreadyInstantiating()) {
3952  // Error out if we hit an instantiation cycle for this initializer.
3953  Diag(PointOfInstantiation, diag::err_default_member_initializer_cycle)
3954  << Instantiation;
3955  return true;
3956  }
3957  PrettyDeclStackTraceEntry CrashInfo(Context, Instantiation, SourceLocation(),
3958  "instantiating default member init");
3959 
3960  // Enter the scope of this instantiation. We don't use PushDeclContext because
3961  // we don't have a scope.
3962  ContextRAII SavedContext(*this, Instantiation->getParent());
3963  EnterExpressionEvaluationContext EvalContext(
3964  *this, Sema::ExpressionEvaluationContext::PotentiallyEvaluated);
3965  ExprEvalContexts.back().DelayedDefaultInitializationContext = {
3966  PointOfInstantiation, Instantiation, CurContext};
3967 
3968  LocalInstantiationScope Scope(*this, true);
3969 
3970  // Instantiate the initializer.
3971  ActOnStartCXXInClassMemberInitializer();
3972  CXXThisScopeRAII ThisScope(*this, Instantiation->getParent(), Qualifiers());
3973 
3974  ExprResult NewInit = SubstInitializer(OldInit, TemplateArgs,
3975  /*CXXDirectInit=*/false);
3976  Expr *Init = NewInit.get();
3977  assert((!Init || !isa<ParenListExpr>(Init)) && "call-style init in class");
3978  ActOnFinishCXXInClassMemberInitializer(
3979  Instantiation, Init ? Init->getBeginLoc() : SourceLocation(), Init);
3980 
3981  if (auto *L = getASTMutationListener())
3982  L->DefaultMemberInitializerInstantiated(Instantiation);
3983 
3984  // Return true if the in-class initializer is still missing.
3985  return !Instantiation->getInClassInitializer();
3986 }

3988 namespace {
3989  /// A partial specialization whose template arguments have matched
3990  /// a given template-id.
3991  struct PartialSpecMatchResult {
3992  ClassTemplatePartialSpecializationDecl *Partial;
3993  TemplateArgumentList *Args;
3994  };
3995 }
3996 
3997 bool Sema::usesPartialOrExplicitSpecialization(
3998  SourceLocation Loc, ClassTemplateSpecializationDecl *ClassTemplateSpec) {
3999  if (ClassTemplateSpec->getTemplateSpecializationKind() ==
4000  TSK_ExplicitSpecialization)
4001  return true;
4002 
4003  SmallVector<ClassTemplatePartialSpecializationDecl *, 4> PartialSpecs;
4004  ClassTemplateSpec->getSpecializedTemplate()
4005  ->getPartialSpecializations(PartialSpecs);
4006  for (unsigned I = 0, N = PartialSpecs.size(); I != N; ++I) {
4007  TemplateDeductionInfo Info(Loc);
4008  if (DeduceTemplateArguments(PartialSpecs[I],
4009  ClassTemplateSpec->getTemplateArgs().asArray(),
4010  Info) == TemplateDeductionResult::Success)
4011  return true;
4012  }
4013 
4014  return false;
4015 }
4016 
4017 /// Get the instantiation pattern to use to instantiate the definition of a
4018 /// given ClassTemplateSpecializationDecl (either the pattern of the primary
4019 /// template or of a partial specialization).
4020 static ActionResult<CXXRecordDecl *>
4021 getPatternForClassTemplateSpecialization(
4022  Sema &S, SourceLocation PointOfInstantiation,
4023  ClassTemplateSpecializationDecl *ClassTemplateSpec,
4024  TemplateSpecializationKind TSK) {
4025  Sema::InstantiatingTemplate Inst(S, PointOfInstantiation, ClassTemplateSpec);
4026  if (Inst.isInvalid())
4027  return {/*Invalid=*/true};
4028  if (Inst.isAlreadyInstantiating())
4029  return {/*Invalid=*/false};
4030 
4031  llvm::PointerUnion<ClassTemplateDecl *,
4032  ClassTemplatePartialSpecializationDecl *>
4033  Specialized = ClassTemplateSpec->getSpecializedTemplateOrPartial();
4034  if (!Specialized.is<ClassTemplatePartialSpecializationDecl *>()) {
4035  // Find best matching specialization.
4036  ClassTemplateDecl *Template = ClassTemplateSpec->getSpecializedTemplate();
4037 
4038  // C++ [temp.class.spec.match]p1:
4039  // When a class template is used in a context that requires an
4040  // instantiation of the class, it is necessary to determine
4041  // whether the instantiation is to be generated using the primary
4042  // template or one of the partial specializations. This is done by
4043  // matching the template arguments of the class template
4044  // specialization with the template argument lists of the partial
4045  // specializations.
4046  typedef PartialSpecMatchResult MatchResult;
4047  SmallVector<MatchResult, 4> Matched;
4048  SmallVector<ClassTemplatePartialSpecializationDecl *, 4> PartialSpecs;
4049  Template->getPartialSpecializations(PartialSpecs);
4050  TemplateSpecCandidateSet FailedCandidates(PointOfInstantiation);
4051  for (unsigned I = 0, N = PartialSpecs.size(); I != N; ++I) {
4052  ClassTemplatePartialSpecializationDecl *Partial = PartialSpecs[I];
4053  TemplateDeductionInfo Info(FailedCandidates.getLocation());
4054  if (TemplateDeductionResult Result = S.DeduceTemplateArguments(
4055  Partial, ClassTemplateSpec->getTemplateArgs().asArray(), Info);
4056  Result != TemplateDeductionResult::Success) {
4057  // Store the failed-deduction information for use in diagnostics, later.
4058  // TODO: Actually use the failed-deduction info?
4059  FailedCandidates.addCandidate().set(
4060  DeclAccessPair::make(Template, AS_public), Partial,
4061  MakeDeductionFailureInfo(S.Context, Result, Info));
4062  (void)Result;
4063  } else {
4064  Matched.push_back(PartialSpecMatchResult());
4065  Matched.back().Partial = Partial;
4066  Matched.back().Args = Info.takeCanonical();
4067  }
4068  }
4069 
4070  // If we're dealing with a member template where the template parameters
4071  // have been instantiated, this provides the original template parameters
4072  // from which the member template's parameters were instantiated.
4073 
4074  if (Matched.size() >= 1) {
4075  SmallVectorImpl<MatchResult>::iterator Best = Matched.begin();
4076  if (Matched.size() == 1) {
4077  // -- If exactly one matching specialization is found, the
4078  // instantiation is generated from that specialization.
4079  // We don't need to do anything for this.
4080  } else {
4081  // -- If more than one matching specialization is found, the
4082  // partial order rules (14.5.4.2) are used to determine
4083  // whether one of the specializations is more specialized
4084  // than the others. If none of the specializations is more
4085  // specialized than all of the other matching
4086  // specializations, then the use of the class template is
4087  // ambiguous and the program is ill-formed.
4088  for (SmallVectorImpl<MatchResult>::iterator P = Best + 1,
4089  PEnd = Matched.end();
4090  P != PEnd; ++P) {
4091  if (S.getMoreSpecializedPartialSpecialization(
4092  P->Partial, Best->Partial, PointOfInstantiation) ==
4093  P->Partial)
4094  Best = P;
4095  }
4096 
4097  // Determine if the best partial specialization is more specialized than
4098  // the others.
4099  bool Ambiguous = false;
4100  for (SmallVectorImpl<MatchResult>::iterator P = Matched.begin(),
4101  PEnd = Matched.end();
4102  P != PEnd; ++P) {
4103  if (P != Best && S.getMoreSpecializedPartialSpecialization(
4104  P->Partial, Best->Partial,
4105  PointOfInstantiation) != Best->Partial) {
4106  Ambiguous = true;
4107  break;
4108  }
4109  }
4110 
4111  if (Ambiguous) {
4112  // Partial ordering did not produce a clear winner. Complain.
4113  Inst.Clear();
4114  ClassTemplateSpec->setInvalidDecl();
4115  S.Diag(PointOfInstantiation,
4116  diag::err_partial_spec_ordering_ambiguous)
4117  << ClassTemplateSpec;
4118 
4119  // Print the matching partial specializations.
4120  for (SmallVectorImpl<MatchResult>::iterator P = Matched.begin(),
4121  PEnd = Matched.end();
4122  P != PEnd; ++P)
4123  S.Diag(P->Partial->getLocation(), diag::note_partial_spec_match)
4124  << S.getTemplateArgumentBindingsText(
4125  P->Partial->getTemplateParameters(), *P->Args);
4126 
4127  return {/*Invalid=*/true};
4128  }
4129  }
4130 
4131  ClassTemplateSpec->setInstantiationOf(Best->Partial, Best->Args);
4132  } else {
4133  // -- If no matches are found, the instantiation is generated
4134  // from the primary template.
4135  }
4136  }
4137 
4138  CXXRecordDecl *Pattern = nullptr;
4139  Specialized = ClassTemplateSpec->getSpecializedTemplateOrPartial();
4140  if (auto *PartialSpec =
4141  Specialized.dyn_cast<ClassTemplatePartialSpecializationDecl *>()) {
4142  // Instantiate using the best class template partial specialization.
4143  while (PartialSpec->getInstantiatedFromMember()) {
4144  // If we've found an explicit specialization of this class template,
4145  // stop here and use that as the pattern.
4146  if (PartialSpec->isMemberSpecialization())
4147  break;
4148 
4149  PartialSpec = PartialSpec->getInstantiatedFromMember();
4150  }
4151  Pattern = PartialSpec;
4152  } else {
4153  ClassTemplateDecl *Template = ClassTemplateSpec->getSpecializedTemplate();
4154  while (Template->getInstantiatedFromMemberTemplate()) {
4155  // If we've found an explicit specialization of this class template,
4156  // stop here and use that as the pattern.
4157  if (Template->isMemberSpecialization())
4158  break;
4159 
4160  Template = Template->getInstantiatedFromMemberTemplate();
4161  }
4162  Pattern = Template->getTemplatedDecl();
4163  }
4164 
4165  return Pattern;
4166 }
4167 
4168 bool Sema::InstantiateClassTemplateSpecialization(
4169  SourceLocation PointOfInstantiation,
4170  ClassTemplateSpecializationDecl *ClassTemplateSpec,
4171  TemplateSpecializationKind TSK, bool Complain) {
4172  // Perform the actual instantiation on the canonical declaration.
4173  ClassTemplateSpec = cast<ClassTemplateSpecializationDecl>(
4174  ClassTemplateSpec->getCanonicalDecl());
4175  if (ClassTemplateSpec->isInvalidDecl())
4176  return true;
4177 
4178  ActionResult<CXXRecordDecl *> Pattern =
4179  getPatternForClassTemplateSpecialization(*this, PointOfInstantiation,
4180  ClassTemplateSpec, TSK);
4181  if (!Pattern.isUsable())
4182  return Pattern.isInvalid();
4183 
4184  return InstantiateClass(
4185  PointOfInstantiation, ClassTemplateSpec, Pattern.get(),
4186  getTemplateInstantiationArgs(ClassTemplateSpec), TSK, Complain);
4187 }

4189 /// Instantiates the definitions of all of the member
4190 /// of the given class, which is an instantiation of a class template
4191 /// or a member class of a template.
4192 void
4193 Sema::InstantiateClassMembers(SourceLocation PointOfInstantiation,
4194  CXXRecordDecl *Instantiation,
4195  const MultiLevelTemplateArgumentList &TemplateArgs,
4196  TemplateSpecializationKind TSK) {
4197  // FIXME: We need to notify the ASTMutationListener that we did all of these
4198  // things, in case we have an explicit instantiation definition in a PCM, a
4199  // module, or preamble, and the declaration is in an imported AST.
4200  assert(
4201  (TSK == TSK_ExplicitInstantiationDefinition ||
4202  TSK == TSK_ExplicitInstantiationDeclaration ||
4203  (TSK == TSK_ImplicitInstantiation && Instantiation->isLocalClass())) &&
4204  "Unexpected template specialization kind!");
4205  for (auto *D : Instantiation->decls()) {
4206  bool SuppressNew = false;
4207  if (auto *Function = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(D)) {
4208  if (FunctionDecl *Pattern =
4209  Function->getInstantiatedFromMemberFunction()) {
4210 
4211  if (Function->isIneligibleOrNotSelected())
4212  continue;
4213 
4214  if (Function->getTrailingRequiresClause()) {
4215  ConstraintSatisfaction Satisfaction;
4216  if (CheckFunctionConstraints(Function, Satisfaction) ||
4217  !Satisfaction.IsSatisfied) {
4218  continue;
4219  }
4220  }
4221 
4222  if (Function->hasAttr<ExcludeFromExplicitInstantiationAttr>())
4223  continue;
4224 
4225  MemberSpecializationInfo *MSInfo =
4226  Function->getMemberSpecializationInfo();
4227  assert(MSInfo && "No member specialization information?");
4228  if (MSInfo->getTemplateSpecializationKind()
4229  == TSK_ExplicitSpecialization)
4230  continue;
4231 
4232  if (CheckSpecializationInstantiationRedecl(PointOfInstantiation, TSK,
4233  Function,
4234  MSInfo->getTemplateSpecializationKind(),
4235  MSInfo->getPointOfInstantiation(),
4236  SuppressNew) ||
4237  SuppressNew)
4238  continue;
4239 
4240  // C++11 [temp.explicit]p8:
4241  // An explicit instantiation definition that names a class template
4242  // specialization explicitly instantiates the class template
4243  // specialization and is only an explicit instantiation definition
4244  // of members whose definition is visible at the point of
4245  // instantiation.
4246  if (TSK == TSK_ExplicitInstantiationDefinition && !Pattern->isDefined())
4247  continue;
4248 
4249  Function->setTemplateSpecializationKind(TSK, PointOfInstantiation);
4250 
4251  if (Function->isDefined()) {
4252  // Let the ASTConsumer know that this function has been explicitly
4253  // instantiated now, and its linkage might have changed.
4254  Consumer.HandleTopLevelDecl(DeclGroupRef(Function));
4255  } else if (TSK == TSK_ExplicitInstantiationDefinition) {
4256  InstantiateFunctionDefinition(PointOfInstantiation, Function);
4257  } else if (TSK == TSK_ImplicitInstantiation) {
4258  PendingLocalImplicitInstantiations.push_back(
4259  std::make_pair(Function, PointOfInstantiation));
4260  }
4261  }
4262  } else if (auto *Var = dyn_cast<VarDecl>(D)) {
4263  if (isa<VarTemplateSpecializationDecl>(Var))
4264  continue;
4265 
4266  if (Var->isStaticDataMember()) {
4267  if (Var->hasAttr<ExcludeFromExplicitInstantiationAttr>())
4268  continue;
4269 
4270  MemberSpecializationInfo *MSInfo = Var->getMemberSpecializationInfo();
4271  assert(MSInfo && "No member specialization information?");
4272  if (MSInfo->getTemplateSpecializationKind()
4273  == TSK_ExplicitSpecialization)
4274  continue;
4275 
4276  if (CheckSpecializationInstantiationRedecl(PointOfInstantiation, TSK,
4277  Var,
4278  MSInfo->getTemplateSpecializationKind(),
4279  MSInfo->getPointOfInstantiation(),
4280  SuppressNew) ||
4281  SuppressNew)
4282  continue;
4283 
4284  if (TSK == TSK_ExplicitInstantiationDefinition) {
4285  // C++0x [temp.explicit]p8:
4286  // An explicit instantiation definition that names a class template
4287  // specialization explicitly instantiates the class template
4288  // specialization and is only an explicit instantiation definition
4289  // of members whose definition is visible at the point of
4290  // instantiation.
4291  if (!Var->getInstantiatedFromStaticDataMember()->getDefinition())
4292  continue;
4293 
4294  Var->setTemplateSpecializationKind(TSK, PointOfInstantiation);
4295  InstantiateVariableDefinition(PointOfInstantiation, Var);
4296  } else {
4297  Var->setTemplateSpecializationKind(TSK, PointOfInstantiation);
4298  }
4299  }
4300  } else if (auto *Record = dyn_cast<CXXRecordDecl>(D)) {
4301  if (Record->hasAttr<ExcludeFromExplicitInstantiationAttr>())
4302  continue;
4303 
4304  // Always skip the injected-class-name, along with any
4305  // redeclarations of nested classes, since both would cause us
4306  // to try to instantiate the members of a class twice.
4307  // Skip closure types; they'll get instantiated when we instantiate
4308  // the corresponding lambda-expression.
4309  if (Record->isInjectedClassName() || Record->getPreviousDecl() ||
4310  Record->isLambda())
4311  continue;
4312 
4313  MemberSpecializationInfo *MSInfo = Record->getMemberSpecializationInfo();
4314  assert(MSInfo && "No member specialization information?");
4315 
4316  if (MSInfo->getTemplateSpecializationKind()
4317  == TSK_ExplicitSpecialization)
4318  continue;
4319 
4320  if (Context.getTargetInfo().getTriple().isOSWindows() &&
4321  TSK == TSK_ExplicitInstantiationDeclaration) {
4322  // On Windows, explicit instantiation decl of the outer class doesn't
4323  // affect the inner class. Typically extern template declarations are
4324  // used in combination with dll import/export annotations, but those
4325  // are not propagated from the outer class templates to inner classes.
4326  // Therefore, do not instantiate inner classes on this platform, so
4327  // that users don't end up with undefined symbols during linking.
4328  continue;
4329  }
4330 
4331  if (CheckSpecializationInstantiationRedecl(PointOfInstantiation, TSK,
4332  Record,
4333  MSInfo->getTemplateSpecializationKind(),
4334  MSInfo->getPointOfInstantiation(),
4335  SuppressNew) ||
4336  SuppressNew)
4337  continue;
4338 
4339  CXXRecordDecl *Pattern = Record->getInstantiatedFromMemberClass();
4340  assert(Pattern && "Missing instantiated-from-template information");
4341 
4342  if (!Record->getDefinition()) {
4343  if (!Pattern->getDefinition()) {
4344  // C++0x [temp.explicit]p8:
4345  // An explicit instantiation definition that names a class template
4346  // specialization explicitly instantiates the class template
4347  // specialization and is only an explicit instantiation definition
4348  // of members whose definition is visible at the point of
4349  // instantiation.
4350  if (TSK == TSK_ExplicitInstantiationDeclaration) {
4351  MSInfo->setTemplateSpecializationKind(TSK);
4352  MSInfo->setPointOfInstantiation(PointOfInstantiation);
4353  }
4354 
4355  continue;
4356  }
4357 
4358  InstantiateClass(PointOfInstantiation, Record, Pattern,
4359  TemplateArgs,
4360  TSK);
4361  } else {
4362  if (TSK == TSK_ExplicitInstantiationDefinition &&
4363  Record->getTemplateSpecializationKind() ==
4364  TSK_ExplicitInstantiationDeclaration) {
4365  Record->setTemplateSpecializationKind(TSK);
4366  MarkVTableUsed(PointOfInstantiation, Record, true);
4367  }
4368  }
4369 
4370  Pattern = cast_or_null<CXXRecordDecl>(Record->getDefinition());
4371  if (Pattern)
4372  InstantiateClassMembers(PointOfInstantiation, Pattern, TemplateArgs,
4373  TSK);
4374  } else if (auto *Enum = dyn_cast<EnumDecl>(D)) {
4375  MemberSpecializationInfo *MSInfo = Enum->getMemberSpecializationInfo();
4376  assert(MSInfo && "No member specialization information?");
4377 
4378  if (MSInfo->getTemplateSpecializationKind()
4379  == TSK_ExplicitSpecialization)
4380  continue;
4381 
4382  if (CheckSpecializationInstantiationRedecl(
4383  PointOfInstantiation, TSK, Enum,
4384  MSInfo->getTemplateSpecializationKind(),
4385  MSInfo->getPointOfInstantiation(), SuppressNew) ||
4386  SuppressNew)
4387  continue;
4388 
4389  if (Enum->getDefinition())
4390  continue;
4391 
4392  EnumDecl *Pattern = Enum->getTemplateInstantiationPattern();
4393  assert(Pattern && "Missing instantiated-from-template information");
4394 
4395  if (TSK == TSK_ExplicitInstantiationDefinition) {
4396  if (!Pattern->getDefinition())
4397  continue;
4398 
4399  InstantiateEnum(PointOfInstantiation, Enum, Pattern, TemplateArgs, TSK);
4400  } else {
4401  MSInfo->setTemplateSpecializationKind(TSK);
4402  MSInfo->setPointOfInstantiation(PointOfInstantiation);
4403  }
4404  } else if (auto *Field = dyn_cast<FieldDecl>(D)) {
4405  // No need to instantiate in-class initializers during explicit
4406  // instantiation.
4407  if (Field->hasInClassInitializer() && TSK == TSK_ImplicitInstantiation) {
4408  CXXRecordDecl *ClassPattern =
4409  Instantiation->getTemplateInstantiationPattern();
4410  DeclContext::lookup_result Lookup =
4411  ClassPattern->lookup(Field->getDeclName());
4412  FieldDecl *Pattern = Lookup.find_first<FieldDecl>();
4413  assert(Pattern);
4414  InstantiateInClassInitializer(PointOfInstantiation, Field, Pattern,
4415  TemplateArgs);
4416  }
4417  }
4418  }
4419 }

4421 /// Instantiate the definitions of all of the members of the
4422 /// given class template specialization, which was named as part of an
4423 /// explicit instantiation.
4424 void
4425 Sema::InstantiateClassTemplateSpecializationMembers(
4426  SourceLocation PointOfInstantiation,
4427  ClassTemplateSpecializationDecl *ClassTemplateSpec,
4428  TemplateSpecializationKind TSK) {
4429  // C++0x [temp.explicit]p7:
4430  // An explicit instantiation that names a class template
4431  // specialization is an explicit instantion of the same kind
4432  // (declaration or definition) of each of its members (not
4433  // including members inherited from base classes) that has not
4434  // been previously explicitly specialized in the translation unit
4435  // containing the explicit instantiation, except as described
4436  // below.
4437  InstantiateClassMembers(PointOfInstantiation, ClassTemplateSpec,
4438  getTemplateInstantiationArgs(ClassTemplateSpec),
4439  TSK);
4440 }

4553 static const Decl *getCanonicalParmVarDecl(const Decl *D) {
4554  // When storing ParmVarDecls in the local instantiation scope, we always
4555  // want to use the ParmVarDecl from the canonical function declaration,
4556  // since the map is then valid for any redeclaration or definition of that
4557  // function.
4558  if (const ParmVarDecl *PV = dyn_cast<ParmVarDecl>(D)) {
4559  if (const FunctionDecl *FD = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(PV->getDeclContext())) {
4560  unsigned i = PV->getFunctionScopeIndex();
4561  // This parameter might be from a freestanding function type within the
4562  // function and isn't necessarily referring to one of FD's parameters.
4563  if (i < FD->getNumParams() && FD->getParamDecl(i) == PV)
4564  return FD->getCanonicalDecl()->getParamDecl(i);
4565  }
4566  }
4567  return D;
4568 }

4571 llvm::PointerUnion<Decl *, LocalInstantiationScope::DeclArgumentPack *> *
4572 LocalInstantiationScope::findInstantiationOf(const Decl *D) {
4573  D = getCanonicalParmVarDecl(D);
4574  for (LocalInstantiationScope *Current = this; Current;
4575  Current = Current->Outer) {
4576 
4577  // Check if we found something within this scope.
4578  const Decl *CheckD = D;
4579  do {
4580  LocalDeclsMap::iterator Found = Current->LocalDecls.find(CheckD);
4581  if (Found != Current->LocalDecls.end())
4582  return &Found->second;
4583 
4584  // If this is a tag declaration, it's possible that we need to look for
4585  // a previous declaration.
4586  if (const TagDecl *Tag = dyn_cast<TagDecl>(CheckD))
4587  CheckD = Tag->getPreviousDecl();
4588  else
4589  CheckD = nullptr;
4590  } while (CheckD);
4591 
4592  // If we aren't combined with our outer scope, we're done.
4593  if (!Current->CombineWithOuterScope)
4594  break;
4595  }
4596 
4597  // If we're performing a partial substitution during template argument
4598  // deduction, we may not have values for template parameters yet.
4599  if (isa<NonTypeTemplateParmDecl>(D) || isa<TemplateTypeParmDecl>(D) ||
4600  isa<TemplateTemplateParmDecl>(D))
4601  return nullptr;
4602 
4603  // Local types referenced prior to definition may require instantiation.
4604  if (const CXXRecordDecl *RD = dyn_cast<CXXRecordDecl>(D))
4605  if (RD->isLocalClass())
4606  return nullptr;
4607 
4608  // Enumeration types referenced prior to definition may appear as a result of
4609  // error recovery.
4610  if (isa<EnumDecl>(D))
4611  return nullptr;
4612 
4613  // Materialized typedefs/type alias for implicit deduction guides may require
4614  // instantiation.
4615  if (isa<TypedefNameDecl>(D) &&
4616  isa<CXXDeductionGuideDecl>(D->getDeclContext()))
4617  return nullptr;
4618 
4619  // If we didn't find the decl, then we either have a sema bug, or we have a
4620  // forward reference to a label declaration. Return null to indicate that
4621  // we have an uninstantiated label.
4622  assert(isa<LabelDecl>(D) && "declaration not instantiated in this scope");
4623  return nullptr;
4624 }

4626 void LocalInstantiationScope::InstantiatedLocal(const Decl *D, Decl *Inst) {
4627  D = getCanonicalParmVarDecl(D);
4628  llvm::PointerUnion<Decl *, DeclArgumentPack *> &Stored = LocalDecls[D];
4629  if (Stored.isNull()) {
4630 #ifndef NDEBUG
4631  // It should not be present in any surrounding scope either.
4632  LocalInstantiationScope *Current = this;
4633  while (Current->CombineWithOuterScope && Current->Outer) {
4634  Current = Current->Outer;
4635  assert(!Current->LocalDecls.contains(D) &&
4636  "Instantiated local in inner and outer scopes");
4637  }
4638 #endif
4639  Stored = Inst;
4640  } else if (DeclArgumentPack *Pack = Stored.dyn_cast<DeclArgumentPack *>()) {
4641  Pack->push_back(cast<VarDecl>(Inst));
4642  } else {
4643  assert(Stored.get<Decl *>() == Inst && "Already instantiated this local");
4644  }
4645 }

4654 void LocalInstantiationScope::MakeInstantiatedLocalArgPack(const Decl *D) {
4655 #ifndef NDEBUG
4656  // This should be the first time we've been told about this decl.
4657  for (LocalInstantiationScope *Current = this;
4658  Current && Current->CombineWithOuterScope; Current = Current->Outer)
4659  assert(!Current->LocalDecls.contains(D) &&
4660  "Creating local pack after instantiation of local");
4661 #endif
4662 
4663  D = getCanonicalParmVarDecl(D);
4664  llvm::PointerUnion<Decl *, DeclArgumentPack *> &Stored = LocalDecls[D];
4665  DeclArgumentPack *Pack = new DeclArgumentPack;
4666  Stored = Pack;

4677 void LocalInstantiationScope::SetPartiallySubstitutedPack(NamedDecl *Pack,
4678  const TemplateArgument *ExplicitArgs,
4679  unsigned NumExplicitArgs) {
4680  assert((!PartiallySubstitutedPack || PartiallySubstitutedPack == Pack) &&
4681  "Already have a partially-substituted pack");
4682  assert((!PartiallySubstitutedPack
4683  || NumArgsInPartiallySubstitutedPack == NumExplicitArgs) &&
4684  "Wrong number of arguments in partially-substituted pack");
4685  PartiallySubstitutedPack = Pack;
4686  ArgsInPartiallySubstitutedPack = ExplicitArgs;
4687  NumArgsInPartiallySubstitutedPack = NumExplicitArgs;

4690 NamedDecl *LocalInstantiationScope::getPartiallySubstitutedPack(
4691  const TemplateArgument **ExplicitArgs,
4692  unsigned *NumExplicitArgs) const {
4693  if (ExplicitArgs)
4694  *ExplicitArgs = nullptr;
4695  if (NumExplicitArgs)
4696  *NumExplicitArgs = 0;
4697 
4698  for (const LocalInstantiationScope *Current = this; Current;
4699  Current = Current->Outer) {
4700  if (Current->PartiallySubstitutedPack) {
4701  if (ExplicitArgs)
4702  *ExplicitArgs = Current->ArgsInPartiallySubstitutedPack;
4703  if (NumExplicitArgs)
4704  *NumExplicitArgs = Current->NumArgsInPartiallySubstitutedPack;
4705 
4706  return Current->PartiallySubstitutedPack;
4707  }
4708 
4709  if (!Current->CombineWithOuterScope)
4710  break;
4711  }
4712 
4713  return nullptr;
4714 }
